Protestors marched in the Ladysmith CBD declaring a complete shut down, this morning (Wednesday, 26 February). Businesses closed their doors for the day as Murchison street came to a standstill. Over 200 people and taxis gathered in front of the Ladysmith Town Hall, demanding that the mayor of Alfred Duma Municipality, Councillor M.V Madlala step down. This is a developing story and updates will follow as events unfold.